metadata.title: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil
aws::graph::propositions: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil Variants and Production
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350B were progressively introduced.
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350 BA were progressively introduced.
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350 B1 were progressively introduced.
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350 B2 were progressively introduced.
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350 B3 were progressively introduced.
The AS350 B3 differed from preceding models by the increasing use of digital systems.
The digital systems in the AS350 B3 included the Garmin-built G500H avionics suite.
The digital systems in the AS350 B3 included the FADEC engine control system.
Prior to 2013, the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil had been manufactured principally at Eurocopter's Marignane facility.
Eurocopter's Marignane facility is located near Marseille, France.
Eurocopter opted to begin AS350 production activities at its factory in Columbus, Mississippi.
Eurocopter opted to begin AS350 final assembly activities at its factory in Columbus, Mississippi.
The production change was part of a move to disperse Eurocopter's helicopter production activities.
The Columbus factory would handle deliveries to U.S. commercial helicopter market.
The Astar has been Eurocopter's biggest-selling product in the US commercial market.
The Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil was at one point selling roughly one AS350 every business day.

text:
Variants of the Arriel-powered AS350B, AS350 BA, AS350 B1, AS350 B2, and AS350 B3, were progressively introduced; the later B3 differing from preceding models by the increasing use of digital systems, such as the Garmin-built G500H avionics suite and FADEC engine control system.
Prior to 2013, the type had been manufactured principally at Eurocopter's Marignane facility, near Marseille, France; Eurocopter opted to, as part of a move to disperse its helicopter production activities, begin AS350 production and final assembly activities at its factory in Columbus, Mississippi, for deliveries to U.S. commercial helicopter market. The Astar has been Eurocopter's biggest-selling product in the US commercial market, at one point selling roughly one AS350 every business day.
